\pard\cf1\f0\fs36 Orbital walls: \cf2 No fracture.\cf1 :\cf2 No fracture.\cf1 /Floor fracture is present. Herniation of orbital fat into the maxillary sinus suspicious for entrapment./Floor fracture is present. No imaging evidence of muscle entrapment./Floor fracture is present. No herniation of orbital contents. No imaging evidence of muscle entrapment./Medial wall fracture is present./Lateral wall fracture is present./Roof fracture is present.\par
\par
Orbital rim: \cf2 Intact.\cf1 :\cf2 Intact.\cf1 /Fracture involving the zygomaticomaxillary complex (ZMC/tripod fracture)./Fracture involving the orbital rim./Fracture involving the \cf2 .\cf1\par
\par
Orbital apex: \cf2 Intact.\cf1 :\cf2 Intact.\cf1 /Fractured. Optic canal: intact. No bony fragment impinging the optic nerve./Fractured. Optic canal: intact. A bony fragment is impinging the optic nerve \emdash  urgent ophthalmology consultation recommended./Fractured. Optic canal: narrowed. No bony fragment impinging the optic nerve./Fractured. Optic canal: narrowed. A bony fragment is impinging the optic nerve \emdash  urgent ophthalmology consultation recommended.\par
\par
