\par
Anterior chamber: \cf2 Normal depth.\cf1 :\cf2 Normal depth.\cf1 /Decreased anterior chamber depth, suggesting corneal laceration or lens subluxation. \cf2 No hyphema.\cf1 :\cf2 No hyphema.\cf1 /Hyphema is present.\par
\par
Lens: \cf2 In normal position.\cf1 :\cf2 In normal position.\cf1 /Posteriorly subluxed / dislocated./Anteriorly subluxed./Complete dislocation into vitreous chamber.\par
\par
Posterior segment: \cf2 No vitreous hemorrhage, retinal detachment, or choroidal detachment.\cf1 :\cf2 No vitreous hemorrhage, retinal detachment, or choroidal detachment.\cf1 /Vitreous hemorrhage is present./V-shaped retinal detachment is present./Lentiform choroidal detachment is present.\par
\par
Intraorbital foreign body: \cf2 None identified.\cf1 :\cf2 None identified.\cf1 /Foreign body is present within the globe./Foreign body is present within the intraconal fat./Foreign body is present within the extraconal fat.\par
\par
Superior ophthalmic vein: \cf2 Normal caliber.\cf1 :\cf2 Normal caliber.\cf1 /Dilated \emdash  carotid-cavernous fistula cannot be excluded; CTA recommended.\par
\par
Optic nerve: \cf2 Normal.\cf1 :\cf2 Normal.\cf1 /Compressed by fracture fragment./Transected.\par
\par
Extraocular muscles: \cf2 Normal.\cf1 :\cf2 Normal.\cf1 /present\cf2 muscle is entrapped / displaced.\cf1\par
\par
Retrobulbar hematoma: \cf2 Absent.\cf1 :\cf2 Absent.\cf1 /Present. Proptosis: \cf2 Absent.\cf1 :\cf2 Absent.\cf1 /Present.\par
\par
